The most recent release of the system is in this directory, named:

    release.tar.gz

To copy the file, right-click on it and select "Save Link (Target) as ..."
in Netscape or "Save Target as ..." in Microsoft Internet Explorer.  Then
browse to the directory to which it is to be copied, and click "Save" (or
"Save as").

To expand the release:

    zcat release.tar.gz | tar -xf -

A directory named Spi-release and a system of sub-directories will be
expanded in the current directory.

A release includes emulators for linux, sgi and solaris platforms.
To install it on one or more of those processors, see the README file in
Spi-release.

Additional documentation for the Logix system is in LogixDocs.

The file:

    update.tar.gz

contains modifications to the release.

Copy it to Spi-release (as above).  Then

    cd Spi-release

and expand the updates by:

    zcat updates.tar.gz | tzr -xf -
    rm */fcp

Finally, re-install for your platform(s).

